  <slide>
    <title>Purpose of AInspector for WCAG Evaluation</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li class="more">Learn about accessibility standards.</li>
        <li class="more">Make hidden accessibility information visible.</li>
        <li class="more">Information on both accessibility features and issues.</li>
        <li class="more">Provide resources for people to learn more about an accessibility requirements.</li>
        <li class="more">Support sharing accessibility evaluation information.</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>AInspector for WCAG Evaluation</title>
    <contents>

      <h2>Version 4.1</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Updated Icon</li>
        <li>In addition to Firefox, support for Chrome, Edge and Opera.</li>
        <li>Updated to use <a href="https://opena11y.github.io/evaluation-library/index.html">OpenA11y Evaluation Library 2.2</a></li>
        <li>Improved highlighting of page and element results.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Installation and Documentation</h2>
      <ul>
       <li>
           <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/ainspector-for-wcag-evalu/dhllbiaionalkdpankidadkoaaenenie">Chrome</a>
        </li>

        <li>
           <a href="https://microsoftedge.microsoft.com/addons/detail/ainspector-for-wcag-evalu/enilnlbjbmnfleppphmbodnhkecoddhg">Edge</a>
        </li>

        <li>
           <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/ainspector-wcag/">Firefox</a>
        </li>

        <li>
           Submitted to Opera Add-ons for review, but is available as a self-hosted version on <a href="https://opena11y.github.io/ainspector/">documentation website</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://opena11y.github.io/ainspector/">More information on AInspector for WCAG Evaluation</a>
        </li>
      </ul>

    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>OpenA11y Evaluation Library 2.2 and Web Standards</title>
    <contents>

      <ul>
        <li>Supports the following W3C standards:
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.2/">Accessible Rich Internet Application (ARIA) 1.2 Specifications</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.3/">Accessible Rich Internet Application (ARIA) 1.3 Specifications</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html-aria/">Accessible Name and Description Computation 1.1</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/accname/">ARIA in HTML Specification</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/">Web content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/">Web content Accessibility Guidelines 2.2</a></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Documentation and Source Code</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://opena11y.github.io/evaluation-library/rulesets.html">Ruleset Information</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/opena11y/evaluation-library">Source Code</a></li>
      </ul>

    </contents>
  </slide>

